<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Mez = big ass aggro, big ass aggro = death, death = not good, therefore mez = not good<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
....<br>
<br>
I have no idea how to respond to that, though a million different responses came to my head, i can't choose one, but IMO is twisted logic.<br>
<br>
<br>
Anyway, to answer the post, I'd rather have summoned mez/charm than summoned 2k nuke.<br>
<br>
New abilities added to a class are the biggest benefit. Look at kunark and luclin. Coth and mod rod 2, basically totally new abilities introduced to us (mod rod 1 is totally different, since it takes more mana to make than it restores) are some of our best abilities.<br>
<br>
Mod rod 2 &gt; SOFB in power, although we could get into a whole extra conversatoin about people not likeing mod rod 2, they can't honestly deny it's omnipotence.<br>
<br>
Anyway, charm/mez way better than summoned only nuke.<br>
<br>
Btw, our charm is good. it has the same resist mod as the druid magic based DoT line. I play a druid and let me tell you, it's a cold day in hell that it's resisted vs appropriate level mobs. I foresee our charm lasting 20 minutes (the max dur. on it) regularly after malosinia.<br>
<br>
Don't ask for the charm to be removed if there are going to be a decent amount of summoned mobs in PoP. Call of the arch mage looks like one hell of a spell. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109465>~Krilen</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rhasinfirestorm>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1085<br> <font color=#333333>(9/25/02 5:06:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 2k anti-summoned nuke &gt; Summoned mez/charm?</span><hr size=1> Lesse...<br>
<br>
Mez = big ass aggro. Fair 'nuf. We have bigass pets at that level, and if it can't get it off you, and the memblur didn't work (30%. Almost 1/3rd of the time it will have forgotten about you).. *shrug* who knows.<br>
<br>
Charm? Heh. that's something I think we mages have had 'under the table' for like a bazillion years. Summon Pet = Create + Perma-nondispellable-Charm. At least, in a roleplayish sense (which, dispite whinings of &quot;is such bogus rationale and not a reason why we should get these things&quot; is pretty much the foundation of why we get our spells in the forms we do).<br>
<br>
While we're not enchanters, we do very much command the power of elementals and summoned creatures at large. It is not a stretch at all to get Summoned Mez/Charm instead of a DD vs summoned. <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886"><IMG SRC="http://www.ninjacorp.com/Rhasin_sig.jpg"></A></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uyanbun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yanbun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 428<br> <font color=#333333>(9/25/02 9:20:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 2k anti-summoned nuke &gt; Summoned mez/charm?</span><hr size=1> The Mez is actually pretty nice. Keep in mind, with this, we are 1 of 4 classes that can Mez. <p>"History is just a set of lies agreed upon" - Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte
